<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, minimal-ui">
    <title>Luna Fire Information</title>
    <link href="styles.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <meta property="og:title" content="Live Updates on #LunaFire" />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta property="og:description" content="Live updates on the #LunaFire near Chacon, New Mexico." />
    <meta property="og:image" content="https://www.lunafire.info/og.jpg" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="column">
          <h1>Luna Fire Information</h1>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="column">
          <p>This website provides up-to-the-minute information on the Luna Fire, in New Mexico's Taos, Mora and Colfax counties. This website is updated every ten minutes. </p>
        </div>
        <div class="column">
          <p>
            <b>Last updated:</b> <%= Time.now.utc.localtime("-06:00").strftime("%b %e, %l:%M %p") %> MDT <br>
            <b>Size:</b> <%= @acreage %> acres<br>
            <b>Containment</b>: 0% <br>
            <b>Personnel on-scene:</b> <%= @personnel %> <br>
            <b>Cause:</b> <%= @cause %>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="column" style="margin-bottom: 2.0rem">
          <details>
            <summary>What is this website?</summary>
            <p>This website aggregates information from many sources on the Luna Fire, which is currently burning in Taos, Mora and Colfax counties in New Mexico.</p>
            <p>This site only posts official fire information and easily verified factual claims (e.g. air assets verified by ADS-B, photos of the fire, etc). It is not affiiliated with any organization, official or unofficial.</p>
            <p>This website is built and maintained by <a href="mailto:nate.berkopec@gmail.com">Nate Berkopec</a>, a resident of the Taos area. It is not official information and should not be quoted directly.</p>
            <p>This is a free and open source project. You can contribute <a href="https://github.com/nateberkopec/lunafire">on GitHub.</a></p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>Sources</summary>
            <ul>
              <li><a href="https://www.fireweatheravalanche.org/wildfire/incident/155594/new-mexico/luna-fire?fbclid=IwAR0GP3NzRT1iLwvhucMHhKUz3xBrtySKYdIS9h5DL1MFcpIX5NlawRP9Cwo-fire">Fire, Weather and Avalanche Center</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://www.facebook.com/CarsonNF">Carson National Forest</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://www.facebook.com/Angel-Fire-Fire-Dept-1063082687042210">Angel Fire Fire Department</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://www.facebook.com/taosnews">Taos News</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://inciweb.nwcg.gov/incident/7246">Inciweb</a></li>
            </ul>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="column">
          <h2>Closures/Evacuations</h2>
          <p>This list is updated manually and may not be up-to-date. Please pay attention to local authorities.</p>
          <ul>
            <li><b>Angel Fire, Black Lake, Hidden Lake, Luna Canyon, Black Canyon and Guadalupita</b> instructed to prepare and plan for evacuation, but evacuation order not issued yet.</li>
            <li><a href="https://www.fs.usda.gov/Internet/FSE_DOCUMENTS/fseprd831990.pdf">The area around the fire is closed.</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://www.fs.usda.gov/Internet/FSE_DOCUMENTS/fseprd832016.pdf">Stage One Fire Restrictions</a> in place for the Carson National Forest beginning 8am October 23.</li>
            <li><b>Eagle Nest Lake</b> is closed to boaters.</li>
          </ul>
          <h2>Recent Developments</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><b>Oct 21</b>: Carson NF <a href="https://www.fs.usda.gov/Internet/FSE_DOCUMENTS/fseprd831990.pdf">implements closure</a> around fire area. <a href="https://www.fs.usda.gov/Internet/FSE_DOCUMENTS/fseprd832016.pdf">Stage 1 Fire Restrictions</a> announced to begin in Carson NF from Oct 23, 8am. 138 personnel on scene. Firefighters strengthening fireline in Frijoles Canyon. Cattle will be moved out of the area today. Source: <a href="https://nmfireinfo.com/2020/10/21/luna-fire-update-oct-21-2020/?fbclid=IwAR2e8Wd37o2pnGZSkw9dSLoEZcE9dHj_QLo_FJA2wSNVZtMv9yC1MWcSYi0">Carson NF</a></li>
            <li><b>Oct 20</b>: A Type-1 Incident Management Team from California will be taking charge of the fire on Oct 21 or 22. Source: <a href="https://www.facebook.com/CarsonNF/posts/3377962862295602">Carson NF</a></li>
            <li><b>Oct 19</b>: Angel Fire mayor asks residents to prepare to evacuate, non-essential businesses to close, and for short-term renters to cancel reservations. Source: <a href="https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=4064269760256806&id=1063082687042210">Angel Fire FD</a></li>
            <li><b>Oct 19</b>: "The Luna Fire is progressing west toward Cerro Vista. Today firefighters focused on the active fire behavior in Luna Canyon, implementing a burn-out operation to protect values at risk." Source: <a href="https://nmfireinfo.com/2020/10/19/luna-fire-update-oct-19-2020/">US Forest Service</a></li>
            <li><b>Oct 19</b>: USFS confirms ~7,000 acres burned. Luna Canyon, Black Canyon and Guadalupita instructed to ready for evacuation. 87 personnel on-scene. Source: <a href="https://www.fs.usda.gov/detail/carson/news-events/?cid=FSEPRD830799">US Forest Service</a></li>
            <li><b>Oct 18</b>: Eagle Nest Lake is closed to boaters. The public is asked to avoid Forest Road 76. Angel Fire is under total outdoor burn ban. Source: <a href="https://www.facebook.com/Angel-Fire-Fire-Dept-1063082687042210">Angel Fire Fire Department</a></li>
            <li><b>Oct 18</b>: Several <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Incident_management_team">Type 1 teams</a>, 6 Large Air Tankers, 2 Very Large Air Tankers, and several helicopters have already responded or are on the way. Source: <a href="https://twitter.com/SWCCNewsNotes">Southwest Coordination Center</a></li>
          </ul>
          
        </div>
        <div class="column maps">
          <h2>Fire Location</h2>
          <iframe src="https://caltopo.com/map.html#ll=36.26753,-105.46875&z=10&b=om&a=modis_p"></iframe>
          <p>
            Distance from: 
            <ul>
              <li><b>Chacon:</b> 2 miles</li>
              <li><b>Taos:</b> 16 miles</li>
              <li><b>Angel Fire:</b> 10 miles</li>
              <li><b>Mora:</b> 16 miles</li>
              <li><b>Valle Escondido:</b> 6 miles</li>
            </ul>
          </p>
          <h2>Fire Situation Map</h2>
          <i>Star icons are infrared/heat detected by satellite. May be delayed by up to 12 hours. Red is most recent, orange/yellow most recent. Lines indicate current winds. Orange dots are structures.</i>
          <iframe src="https://sartopo.com/map.html#ll=36.22433,-105.35717&z=11&b=om&a=structures%2Cmodis_mp%2Cwxd_wspd-01"></iframe>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="column"> 
          <h2>Featured Photos</h2>
          <i>Please wait for images to load</i>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="column">
          <%= @featured.first.to_s %>
        </div>
        <div class="column">
          <%= @featured.last.to_s %>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="column"> 
          <h2>Live Updates</h2>
          <i>Please wait for images to load</i>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="column">
          <% @feed_items.each_slice(2).map(&:first).each do |i| %>
            <%= i.to_s %>
          <% end %>
        </div>
        <div class="column">
          <% @feed_items.each_slice(2).map(&:last).each do |i| %>
            <%= i.to_s %>
          <% end %>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
